Business Brief -- Dial Corp.:
   Spinoff of GFC Financial
   Approved by Shareholders
Chairman John W. Teets said all regulatory and bank
approvals needed for the transaction have been obtained and
that the legal steps are almost complete.
   Dial, a consumer products, financial services and
manufacturing concern, said today is the record date for the
distribution. Dial's common will continue to trade through
March 18, by which time Dial plans to mail out certificates
for the new GFC Financial stock. After that, new Dial stock
and the GFC Financial stock will both trade on the New York
Stock Exchange, a company spokeswoman said. Holders of the
new Dial stock will not be entitled to the GFC Financial
stock distribution.